      "Contract employee transported to Lafayette General for treatment",
      "BSEE Lafayette District Inspector conducted onsite investigation on June 8, 2019",
      "Lessee waiting on engineering and construction to clear low beam from escape route"
    ],
    "summary": "On May 24, 2019 at approximately 1600 hours, a contract employee was injured while attempting to carry a handrail section to the +10 level. As the employee walked down the southeast stairwell carrying the handrail, it connected with an existing stairwell handrail. The employee lost his footing while attempting to free the handrail and fell down the remaining stairwell. During the fall, his face and head struck a low clearance support beam. The employee sustained a broken nose and broken facial bones and was transported to Lafayette General for treatment.",
    "recommendations": [
      "BSEE Lafayette District office made no recommendations to the Regional Office of Incident Investigations"
    ],
